Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.38,0:00:58.89,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,The Oracle's words stand as a warning.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.60,0:01:00.60,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,A prophecy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.52,0:01:04.31,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Sparta will fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.81,0:01:07.55,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,All of Greece will fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.36,0:01:17.99,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,And Persian fire will reduce Athens to cinder.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.74,0:01:21.29,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,For Athens is a pile of stone and wood...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.54,0:01:23.20,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...and cloth and dust...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.75,0:01:27.41,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...and, as dust, will vanish into the wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.75,0:01:30.29,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Only the Athenians themselves exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.54,0:01:33.55,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,And the fate of the world hangs  on their every syllable.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.47,0:01:41.68,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Only the Athenians exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.68,0:01:46.14,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,And only stout wooden ships can save them.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.89,0:01:49.56,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Wooden ships...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.15,0:01:52.44,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...and a tidal wave of heroes' blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.03,0:02:04.70,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Leonidas, my husband...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.41,0:02:06.96,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...Leonidas, your king...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.62,0:02:12.29,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...Leonidas and the brave 300 are dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.59,0:02:15.21,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,The free men and women of Greece...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.46,0:02:18.22,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...are not bound by  a beautiful Spartan death.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.59,0:02:20.59,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,War is not their love.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.84,0:02:23.18,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Yet he lay down his life for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.43,0:02:25.39,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,For the promise Greece holds.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.14,0:02:32.15,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,'Tis our enemies who forged our freedom  in the fires of war.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.27,0:02:36.36,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,It was King Darius  who came to take our land.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.44,0:02:40.74,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Ten years ago,  when youth still burned in our eyes...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.07,0:02:44.78,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...before this bitter war forced our children  to become men.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.41,0:02:50.33,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Ten years ago, this war began...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.58,0:02:52.58,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...as all wars begin:
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.38,0:02:55.21,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,With a grievance.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.22,0:02:59.72,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Marathon.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.13,0:03:02.97,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,The Persian king, Darius...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.47,0:03:05.89,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...annoyed by the notion of Greek freedom...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.72,0:03:09.06,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...has come to Greece to bring us to heel.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.60,0:03:13.69,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,He makes landfall at the field of Marathon...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.94,0:03:16.36,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...with an invading force  which outnumbers...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.61,0:03:18.57,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...the Greek defenders three-to-one.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.82,0:03:21.95,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,And so at dawn, the hopeless Athenians  do the unthinkable.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.74,0:03:24.24,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,They attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.49,0:03:26.87,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,They attack the weary Persians  as they disembark...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.12,0:03:30.58,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...their ships  on shaky legs after a month at sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.54,0:03:34.04,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,They attack before they can  establish their war camp...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.29,0:03:35.75,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...and supply their soldiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.75,0:03:37.75,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,And who...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.00,0:03:40.38,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...is the architect of this mad strategy?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.01,0:03:41.97,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,A little-known Athenian...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.22,0:03:43.72,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...soldier.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.64,0:03:46.22,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,His men call him...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.47,0:03:48.27,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...Themistokles.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.51,0:03:52.13,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,He gives the Persians a taste  of Athenian shock combat.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.58,0:06:16.16,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,All thoughts of glory are gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.75,0:06:18.71,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Thousands dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.42,0:06:20.96,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Hundreds of them their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.88,0:06:27.30,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,A free Greece...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.55,0:06:30.47,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...an Athenian experiment  called "democracy. "{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.10,0:06:35.39,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Could this idea be worth it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.60,0:06:39.31,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Worth all this sacrifice?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.40,0:06:43.73,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Themistokles would let  the good King Darius decide.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.03,0:06:48.65,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,For through the chaos...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.90,0:06:50.45,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...a moment appeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.99,0:06:55.66,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,And Themistokles would seize it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.88,0:07:07.92,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,A moment...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.17,0:07:09.97,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...that would ring across the centuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.22,0:07:11.22,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,A moment that would...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.47,0:07:13.22,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...raise him from simple soldier...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.47,0:07:15.64,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...to the height of Athenian political power.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.89,0:07:18.43,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.85,0:07:24.27,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,A moment that would make  Themistokles a legend.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.04,0:07:44.67,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Yet even as the praise and glory...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.92,0:07:46.75,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...were heaped upon him...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.00,0:07:49.92,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Themistokles knew in his heart  he had made a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.17,0:07:53.80,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,It was Darius' son, Xerxes...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.05,0:07:56.47,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...whose eyes had the stink  of destiny about them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.56,0:08:01.06,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Themistokles knew  he should have killed that boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.94,0:08:06.02,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,That glorious mistake  would forever haunt him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.32,0:08:14.03,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,And so it was Themistokles himself...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.28,0:08:17.37,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...who sent a ripple  across the Persian empire...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.62,0:08:19.33,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...and set into motion...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.58,0:08:22.29,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...forces that would bring fire  to the heart of Greece.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.00,0:08:26.92,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,For as the good king lay dying...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.17,0:08:28.63,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...all his greatest generals...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.88,0:08:31.88,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...and advisors  were summoned to his bedside.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.22,0:08:33.38,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,None greater...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.63,0:08:37.35,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...than his finest  naval commander, Artemisia.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.76,0:08:40.43,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Her ferocity bested only by her beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.68,0:08:43.94,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Her beauty matched only  by her devotion to her king.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.07,0:08:52.32,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Darius favored Arfemisia  among his generals...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.57,0:08:55.49,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...for she had brought him victory  on the battlefield.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.11,0:08:57.28,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,In her...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.53,0:09:00.45,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...he had the perfect warrior protegee...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.70,0:09:02.62,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...that his son, Xerxes, would never be.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.83,0:09:10.21,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,So sweet, my child.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.21,0:09:13.01,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,My sweet...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.76,0:09:15.38,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...child.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.77,0:09:25.27,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.98,0:09:27.52,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Xerxes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.02,0:09:31.40,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Do not repeat your father's mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.73,0:09:36.40,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave the ignoble Greeks to their ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.53,0:09:40.66,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Only the gods can defeat them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.58,0:09:44.66,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Only the gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.72,0:09:58.76,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,For seven days, Xerxes mourned...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.01,0:10:01.09,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,paralyzed by grief.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.35,0:10:04.68,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,On the eighth day, Artemisia  whispered the seed of madness...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.93,0:10:06.68,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...that would consume him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.94,0:10:10.69,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Your father's words were not a warning...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.48,0:10:13.11,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...but a challenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.61,0:10:17.53,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Only the gods can defeat the Greeks?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.11,0:10:24.12,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,You will be a god-king.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.46,0:10:30.75,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Artemisia gathered the priests, wizards...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.00,0:10:34.09,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...and mystics  from every corner of the empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.50,0:10:35.63,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,They wrapped”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.88,0:10:39.26,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...the young king in Cimmerian gauze  dipped in ancient potions...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.68,0:10:42.05,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...and set him to wander the desert...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.26,0:10:46.52,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...till in a delirium of heat and thirst,  he stumbled upon...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.77,0:10:48.14,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...a hermit's cave.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.10,0:10:54.65,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Xerxes passed the vacant eyes...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.90,0:10:56.32,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...and empty souls...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.57,0:11:00.57,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...of the hollow creatures that dwell  in the dark corners of all men's hearts.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.16,0:11:05.28,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,And in that darkness...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.62,0:11:08.45,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...he surrendered himself completely...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.70,0:11:11.75,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...to power so evil and perverse...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.38,0:11:17.09,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...that, as he emerged...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.34,0:11:20.68,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...no part of a human man  that was Xerxes survived.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.31,0:11:32.52,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,His eyes blazed like scarlet coals.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.40,0:11:38.32,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,He was stripped, cleansed, glabrous...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.57,0:11:40.07,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...and smooth.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.99,0:11:43.24,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Xerxes was reborn...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.49,0:11:44.95,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...a god.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.29,0:11:52.46,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Artemisia trusted no one.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.17,0:11:55.04,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,So in the cover of night...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.29,0:11:59.05,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...the palace was cleansed  of all Xerxes' allies.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.38,0:12:04.09,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,All those he trusted...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.77,0:12:11.02,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...all those who had raised him...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.81,0:12:18.15,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...all those he had  once looked to for counsel...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.98,0:12:22.74,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...were quickly introduced to her wrath.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.47,0:12:49.97,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,And as the god-king stood...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.22,0:12:51.89,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...before his people...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.06,0:12:55.90,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...Anemisia watched her flawless  manipulation take shape.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.15,0:12:58.90,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,- For glory's sake...  - For glory's sake...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.15,0:13:01.74,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,-...for vengeance's sake...  -...for vengeance's sake...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.99,0:13:05.28,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...war.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.86,0:13:07.32,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,---War!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.08,0:13:12.62,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,War is coming to Greece...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.87,0:13:16.37,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...in the visage of a monster army  over a million strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.25,0:13:20.46,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,It should be little more than a formality  for Themistokles...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.71,0:13:22.38,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...the hero of Marathon...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.63,0:13:24.67,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...to finish what he began.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.88,0:13:29.43,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Please! We must appeal to Xerxes' reason!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.68,0:13:30.72,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Coward!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.97,0:13:33.22,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Athens is a city of cowards!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.47,0:13:34.02,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut your cock hole!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.27,0:13:35.35,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut your own!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.60,0:13:37.56,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll kill you! Fuck the Spartans!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.81,0:13:39.44,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Fuck those muscle-bound boy-lovers!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.69,0:13:40.40,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Silence!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.65,0:13:42.19,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Silence for the hero of Marathon!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.44,0:13:44.95,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a democracy, not a street fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.19,0:13:46.99,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Quiet! It's Themistokles.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.24,0:13:50.82,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,The Persian attack will come  from both the north and the south.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.08,0:13:53.66,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,The city-states should negotiate a truce.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.91,0:13:56.29,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, yes, we must negotiate.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.29,0:13:58.87,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Negotiate with tyranny?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.08,0:14:03.00,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Give me one example of when  that has ever profited a nation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.21,0:14:06.05,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,- You're right. We must unite.  - My fellow countrymen...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.76,0:14:09.43,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...we can only judge the future...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.68,0:14:12.35,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...from what we have suffered in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.72,0:14:16.35,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, many of you here  stood with me at Marathon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.52,0:14:19.52,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,And for those of you who served...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.77,0:14:21.90,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...and faced the cut  and thrust of battle...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.15,0:14:24.69,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...you know how true peace is forged.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.61,0:14:27.32,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Do not be deceived.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.57,0:14:29.61,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Xerxes, the son of Darius...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.86,0:14:31.95,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...is a wolf at our door.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.74,0:14:34.91,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Right here, right now...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.79,0:14:37.50,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...we must choose:
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.91,0:14:40.58,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Do we stand and fight for Greece or not?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.75,0:14:42.92,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Argos...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.17,0:14:44.34,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...Corinth...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.59,0:14:45.76,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...Megara...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.01,0:14:47.63,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...Athens.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.88,0:14:50.34,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Not even Sparta  can match the Persians alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.59,0:14:52.80,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,We must persevere as one nation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.05,0:14:55.31,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Or we will perish clinging onto...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.56,0:14:57.22,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...our own self-interests.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.35,0:15:01.69,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Send us the ships that we need  to defend Greece.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.94,0:15:04.36,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Themistokles will need more  than our cities' ships.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.61,0:15:06.60,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,He will need our children  to join the fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.65,0:15:10.03,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,And what of Sparta?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.28,0:15:13.12,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,You send every ship that we have...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.37,0:15:15.70,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...to the northern coast of Euboea.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.95,0:15:20.83,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,I will go and seek the help  of the great Spartans.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.48,0:15:43.48,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Still no word...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.73,0:15:46.19,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...from the messenger  you sent to Sparta.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.86,0:15:49.99,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,King Leonidas may have been insulted  by your generous offer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.24,0:15:54.20,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps I need to march into Sparta myself  and burn it to the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.16,0:15:57.66,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Remember...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.91,0:15:59.62,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...when a king is loved as I am...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.08,0:16:03.33,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...much can be accomplished.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.88,0:16:08.21,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,They would be fools  to resist my divine power.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.46,0:16:11.26,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Athens is attempting to assemble a coalition.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.51,0:16:13.97,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be nothing more  than a patchwork of ships.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.18,0:16:19.97,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Once these waters have been traversed,  I will lead my force across the land.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.22,0:16:22.56,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,I will remind the cowards of Greece...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.81,0:16:26.23,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...that we have not forgotten their insolence.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.16,0:16:37.95,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Rest and water the horses.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.20,0:16:39.62,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,It's best I go alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.87,0:16:43.29,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Spartans don't get along well with others.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.76,0:17:36.55,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,- Spartans.  - Themistokles.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.93,0:17:39.39,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,You old snake.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.64,0:17:42.47,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,- What brings you this far south?  - I've come to see Leonidas.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.72,0:17:45.64,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,- To warn him that the Persians are on the march.  - You're too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.89,0:17:49.06,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Persian messenger already presented  his terms to Leonidas.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.81,0:17:52.19,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Symbolic offering of earth and water.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.83,0:18:02.20,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Spartans!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.45,0:18:04.16,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Know this and know it well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.00,0:18:07.58,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,That any Spartan's finest moment...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.33,0:18:09.75,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...the greatest fulfillment...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.00,0:18:11.84,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...of all he holds dear...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.09,0:18:13.38,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...is that moment...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.63,0:18:15.76,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...when he has fought his heart out...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.01,0:18:18.84,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...for the preservation of Sparta...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.09,0:18:22.43,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...and lies dead on the battlefield...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.68,0:18:24.39,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...victorious.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.18,0:18:27.43,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.94,0:18:31.36,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...who is willing to die at our king's side?  Ah-ooh!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.61,0:18:33.86,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah-ooh! Ah-ooh!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.48,0:18:36.07,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Themistokles.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.03,0:18:41.95,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,You've come a long way to stroke your cock  whilst watching real men train.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.20,0:18:43.24,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Queen Gorgo.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.41,0:18:47.37,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Shouldn't he be training them  to live at their king's side?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.96,0:18:50.25,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,A new age is dawning, Gorgo.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.25,0:18:56.09,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Won't be long before men rise up  and shed the yoke of mysticism and tyranny.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.34,0:18:58.80,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,- That sounds like a threat.  - No.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.22,0:19:02.89,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,An opportunity to join the rest of free Greece  and stand against a true tyrant.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.51,0:19:08.14,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Unless, of course, you and Leonidas  have already made a deal with Xerxes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.39,0:19:10.14,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,No terms were reached.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.73,0:19:12.60,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Xerxes' messenger was...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.86,0:19:15.32,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, he was rude and he lacked respect.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.57,0:19:19.57,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,He didn't understand the same threats made  in Thebes and Athens would not work here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.32,0:19:23.66,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the birthplace  of the world's greatest warriors.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.95,0:19:28.75,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Men whose king would stand  and fight and die for any one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.79,0:19:31.00,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Xerxes' messenger...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.25,0:19:34.46,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...did not understand  this is no typical Greek city-state.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.55,0:19:39.38,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Sparta.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.76,0:19:43.64,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,It was clear to the messenger  there'd be no Spartan submission?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.89,0:19:44.93,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,It was clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.18,0:19:48.47,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Even now Leonidas is in counsel  with the Oracle over his battle plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.72,0:19:51.39,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,The Festival of the Carneia  is all that stands in our way.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.64,0:19:54.35,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Surely the Oracle will see we must fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.61,0:19:56.19,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, then my timing is perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.98,0:20:00.15,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,I am commanding a fleet of ships  that will represent a united Greece.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.40,0:20:02.66,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,I need Sparta to join me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.57,0:20:04.99,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Give me your ships, Gorgo.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.24,0:20:08.08,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll make sure that Xerxes wishes  he never crossed the Aegean.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.33,0:20:11.58,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll receive no Spartan ships.  We've no interest in a united Greece.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.83,0:20:14.42,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,That is your dream, Themistokles, not ours.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.04,0:20:17.17,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,All I am concerned with  is the preservation...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.42,0:20:18.54,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...of Sparta.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.71,0:20:21.63,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,My guards will see you out.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.01,0:20:25.64,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,It's funny that you mock freedom...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.89,0:20:27.76,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...here in your selfish isolation.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.72,0:20:30.85,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Yet freedom, in her wisdom...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.10,0:20:33.39,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...has chosen you to defend her.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.44,0:20:37.65,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,MY queen.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.24,0:20:43.40,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Will Sparta join our fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.74,0:20:47.74,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently the Persians have offered  the Spartans something they cannot refuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.74,0:20:49.94,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,And what is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.24,0:20:51.91,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,A beautiful death.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.22,0:21:13.52,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,They say you are the bravest  of our captives.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.10,0:21:17.60,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,They say you are a whore  from the eastern seas.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.03,0:21:23.61,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not the smartest.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.03,0:21:28.03,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Your commander is a Greek.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.28,0:21:30.24,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Just like me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.54,0:21:34.79,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,You Persian men take your orders  from a Greek woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.04,0:21:38.38,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, my brother, I am Greek by birth...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.63,0:21:41.67,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...and I have Greek blood  running through my veins.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.38,0:21:46.13,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,But my heart...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.64,0:21:49.92,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...is Persian.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.38,0:22:23.79,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Within hours...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.51,0:22:26.88,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...the Greek fleet will be shattered.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.13,0:22:29.93,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,What of our master  and the much-feared Spartans?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.18,0:22:32.30,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing to fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.89,0:22:36.77,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Only King Leonidas  and his personal guard of 300...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.02,0:22:39.05,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...have marched to fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.27,0:22:40.30,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,They'll collapse. Instantly.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.65,0:22:44.65,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,You.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.32,0:22:52.78,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you agree?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.33,0:22:56.70,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Many will perish.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.12,0:23:01.25,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Your confidence leaves me  with a strong impression.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.75,0:23:04.92,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a curious thing for a simple ship guard...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.17,0:23:07.92,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...to not lower his eyes  when questioned by me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.05,0:23:11.80,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,That could've been just a lack of discipline.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.01,0:23:15.47,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,But a man's hands do not lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.72,0:23:16.81,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,They can reveal...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.06,0:23:21.06,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...every imperfection  and flaw in his character.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.02,0:23:23.98,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,You see, your hands  are not rough enough...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.23,0:23:26.27,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...to work the rigging of this ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.82,0:23:30.57,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,I know every single man beneath my lash.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.82,0:23:34.62,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you explain to me  how I don't know you?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.45,0:23:38.66,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive me, commander.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.37,0:23:43.38,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me introduce myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.04,0:23:45.83,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Seize the spy.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.23,0:24:07.02,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Coward.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.03,0:24:09.94,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Storm is upon us.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.78,0:24:15.66,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just some mad Greek weather.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.21,0:24:30.47,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,- Themistokles.  - Come.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.01,0:24:35.30,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Calisto.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.55,0:24:38.14,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,What is spoken here must not be repeated.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.60,0:24:39.81,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.73,0:24:45.94,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,My son has not earned the right  to sit at the table of combat veterans.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.19,0:24:48.57,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,- But you can trust him.  - Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.48,0:24:52.32,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,- Tell me.  - A Greek woman...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.57,0:24:54.86,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...commands all of Xerxes' ships  to the south.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.28,0:24:57.91,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Artemisia.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.91,0:24:59.91,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,I know of her.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.95,0:25:03.87,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Artemisia is murderous by trade  with true skill on the sea...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.12,0:25:05.92,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...and she has thirst for vengeance.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.54,0:25:08.04,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Rumors are her entire family...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.29,0:25:10.59,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...was murdered  by a squad of Greek hoplites.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.67,0:25:14.13,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,I have heard all the stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.22,0:25:18.00,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,And the hoplites spared no one on that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.29,0:25:46.37,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,The story goes  that they raped and murdered...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.62,0:25:48.08,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...her entire family.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.13,0:25:53.05,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,And then they turned their attention  towards her.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.90,0:26:19.41,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,After years of being kept in the bowels  of a Greek slave ship...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.57,0:26:23.12,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...she was discarded and left for dead...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.08,0:26:26.66,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...where she was found near death  by a Persian emissary.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.89,0:26:50.48,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Artemisia vowed that day  to return to Greece...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.94,0:26:53.65,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...only when she could watch it burn.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.24,0:27:08.83,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,She was fed, clothed, trained  by the finest warriors of the Persian empire...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.92,0:27:14.38,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...until no match could be found...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.63,0:27:15.84,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...for her skills and gift with the sword.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.07,0:27:46.58,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,The great King Darius was impressed  by her commitment.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.87,0:27:50.08,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,And she quickly rose to command  at his side.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.83,0:27:55.46,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,She has sold her soul...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.71,0:27:57.17,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...to Death himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.51,0:28:00.84,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, some could say  that I've sold mine to Greece.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.10,0:28:06.10,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,And what do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.35,0:28:08.06,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,- Me?  - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.31,0:28:10.18,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,You are the future of this country.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.23,0:28:12.60,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm ready to fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.11,0:28:18.57,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,I like him. He reminds me of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.36,0:28:20.03,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,We will need...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.28,0:28:21.07,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...every last man.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.32,0:28:22.40,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,He is still just a boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.65,0:28:23.99,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Much younger...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.24,0:28:26.03,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,-...have defended our country.  - Enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.49,0:28:29.24,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,You are a dreamer  and will speak of this no more.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.08,0:28:35.08,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Themistokles, I've set your plan in motion.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.33,0:28:38.25,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,And my land force  will be assembled by the second day.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.50,0:28:41.34,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,You will be needed.  I can assure you of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.14,0:28:47.05,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,And there is bad news.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.30,0:28:50.27,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Leonidas has marched north  to the Hot Gates.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.06,0:28:54.02,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Bad news? With the Spartans...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.27,0:28:58.11,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,- ...at the Hot Gates, our victory is assured.  - If the army were with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.11,0:29:01.03,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,But between the Oracle and the Carneia...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.28,0:29:03.90,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...Leonidas has marched to Thermopylae  with just 300 men.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.07,0:29:08.53,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,So the only thing standing between Athens...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.78,0:29:10.29,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...and total annihilation...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.33,0:29:13.91,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...is Leonidas and 300 Spartans.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.75,0:29:20.84,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,I will search out the veterans among them.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.09,0:29:23.84,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,- Establish some order among the volunteers.  - Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.55,0:29:27.68,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,There's little time  to teach these farmhands strategy.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.26,0:29:30.30,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Just keep them well fed...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.27,0:29:32.64,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...and sober.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.31,0:29:34.73,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Anything else?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.27,0:29:37.19,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Wouldn't hurt if they could  swing a sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.11,0:29:41.82,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'll be damned.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.28,0:29:44.28,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Shit.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.53,0:29:47.45,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,- Does your father know that you're here?  - No, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.70,0:29:49.74,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,And this shield and sword?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.99,0:29:51.49,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,My grandfather's.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.74,0:29:54.54,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,My mother entrusted them to me  this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.04,0:29:58.33,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,- When she gave you her blessing?  - Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.96,0:30:01.21,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,With a sharp blade, no less.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.00,0:30:05.84,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Your father is preparing a surprise  for our enemy tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.09,0:30:09.43,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,I choose to fight here. Now.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.51,0:30:13.26,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Come aboard my ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.89,0:30:15.27,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,That is where you will fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.52,0:30:16.77,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.06,0:30:22.32,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,We've just over 50 ships.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.57,0:30:25.32,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Persian forces reported a number  in the thousands.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.57,0:30:28.91,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,- Those ships appear hardly seaworthy.  - Nothing like the monster ships...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.16,0:30:32.45,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,-...of the Persian fleet.  - We have the advantage. Speed, maneuverability.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.74,0:30:36.45,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,The rest of the city-states have sent  anywhere from a handful to a single ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.71,0:30:40.00,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,- Of course, Athens supplied the balance.  - We have report...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.25,0:30:44.25,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...a small advance force of Persian ships have  taken refuge from the storm across the strait.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.55,0:30:46.84,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,If the weather breaks,  we could hit them at dawn.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.72,0:30:49.76,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,An early Greek victory.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.01,0:30:51.80,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,The gods have given us an opportunity...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.05,0:30:54.01,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...to wound the Persians,  strengthen Greek morale.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.18,0:30:57.31,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,A tempting distraction.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.56,0:30:59.64,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,But we'll stick to the battle plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.90,0:31:03.02,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Today at sundown, we will sail out  to meet the main Persian fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.27,0:31:06.32,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll attack in the open water  with no shore to narrow the battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.57,0:31:08.40,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,To attack a force of over 1000 ships...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.65,0:31:10.45,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...with our meager force is suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.99,0:31:13.95,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Such is my plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.12,0:31:20.71,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at their excuse for a navy.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.58,0:31:23.96,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Their ships are of little threat.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.84,0:31:27.09,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,I need a second in command, Artaphernes.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.34,0:31:31.34,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,And whoever proves their excellence  will earn a place beside me.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.76,0:31:35.60,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,General Bandari has offered  to lead the first attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.85,0:31:37.06,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Bandafi.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.85,0:31:40.94,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Commander.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.19,0:31:43.11,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,If I let you lead our first offensive...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.35,0:31:46.40,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...what guarantee do I have  that you'll bring me a quick victory?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.65,0:31:48.57,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,My word and my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.15,0:31:50.15,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.70,0:31:52.24,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,My rules of engagement?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.86,0:31:56.53,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Humiliate the Greeks  and lay waste to their tiny ships.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.54,0:31:59.95,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,They'll be dead to the last man.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.59,0:32:12.22,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,My brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.72,0:32:14.72,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Steady your hearts.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.55,0:32:18.22,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Look deep into your souls.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.48,0:32:25.56,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,For your mettle is to be tested this day.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.40,0:32:31.65,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,If in the heat of battle...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.03,0:32:35.70,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,you need a reason to fight on...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.83,0:32:39.54,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...an idea for which you will give up...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.16,0:32:42.41,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...all that you will ever have...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.62,0:32:46.58,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...you need only to look at the man  who fights at your side.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.55,0:32:51.05,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the "why" of battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.30,0:32:54.09,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the brotherhood of men-at-arms.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.13,0:32:56.59,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,An unbreakable bond...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.84,0:32:59.85,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...made stronger by the crucible of combat.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.31,0:33:05.06,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,You will never be closer than with those  who you shed your blood with.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.02,0:33:09.11,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,For there is no nobler cause...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.36,0:33:12.69,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...than to fight for those  who will la y down their life for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.70,0:33:17.11,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,So you fight strong today.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.24,0:33:20.33,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,You fight for your brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.62,0:33:23.66,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Fight for your families.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.46,0:33:26.46,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Most of all, you fight for Greece!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.71,0:33:27.74,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Greece!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.79,0:33:29.79,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.01,0:33:35.30,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,And there is only one thing to make sure of  when the fighting starts.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.55,0:33:36.59,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.68,0:33:39.51,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get killed on the first day.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.01,0:33:43.23,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,That goes for the rest of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.92,0:34:15.67,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Persian ships...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.92,0:34:17.43,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...are strong at the front.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.68,0:34:18.68,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,But they are weak...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.93,0:34:20.34,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...in the middle.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.60,0:34:22.43,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,We attack them there.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.69,0:34:34.36,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,NOW!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.38,0:34:56.46,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.66,0:35:26.03,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Ram them!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.96,0:35:40.05,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Archers, now! Now!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.31,0:35:50.77,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Reverse!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.10,0:35:52.52,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,NOW!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.32,0:36:00.70,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Go through them!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.58,0:36:56.84,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,The enemy's tactics...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.08,0:36:58.46,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...are creative.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.71,0:37:01.13,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,The defensive circle  leaves no front to assault.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.72,0:37:03.09,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,We are losing.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.34,0:37:05.01,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,No, you are losing.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.47,0:37:12.85,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Pull back.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.35,0:37:15.02,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Let them have this day.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.65,0:37:18.69,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm bored with your failures, Bandari.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.86,0:37:26.16,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll not let this wound slow me.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.16,0:37:28.41,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Heh. Somehow I believe you.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.66,0:37:30.87,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,My blade will be sharp and ready  by the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.87,0:37:34.54,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Good. Tomorrow you will fight  alongside your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.62,0:37:37.63,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Not bad...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.88,0:37:41.34,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,-...for a bunch of farmers.  - And poets and sculptors.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.59,0:37:43.05,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Who'd have known untrained men...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.30,0:37:46.09,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...would do so well against  such a considerable adversary?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.47,0:37:51.72,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to need all of our strength  for tomorrow's fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.35,0:37:54.56,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,How long do you think we can hold them?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.52,0:37:59.77,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,If my plan is to work...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.61,0:38:04.65,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...long enough for the Spartans  to unite Greece.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.95,0:38:07.24,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Men!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.78,0:38:10.19,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Who will share their wine with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.96,0:38:24.05,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Report.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.30,0:38:26.09,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,We are still tallying the losses.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.72,0:38:29.30,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,But you must understand,  it is extremely difficult...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.55,0:38:31.89,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...given the sea and the darkness...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.14,0:38:33.75,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...to get an accurate--
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.94,0:38:46.07,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Report?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.69,0:38:48.11,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Seventy-five ships lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.36,0:38:49.74,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Thirty damaged beyond repair.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.99,0:38:53.03,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Twenty could return with a few weeks' work  in a safe harbor.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.20,0:39:00.12,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,The commander of the Greek force  is named Themistokles.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.37,0:39:02.38,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, he is an Athenian general.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.21,0:39:05.05,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,He's rumored to have loosed the arrow...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.30,0:39:07.84,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...that felled the great King Darius himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.40,0:39:22.36,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.00,0:39:41.00,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,This Themistokles has shown himself  to be quite brilliant in battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.63,0:39:44.71,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Which is more than I can say for any of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.09,0:39:49.30,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you gentlemen find my command  unreasonable?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.76,0:39:52.42,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it too much to ask for victory?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.55,0:39:56.14,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Your disappointment in yesterday's losses...  ...is warranted.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.60,0:39:59.60,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,My disappointment.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.94,0:40:03.35,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,My disappointment is not with my losses.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.60,0:40:07.23,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,The meager number of damaged ships  and dead slaves means nothing to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.48,0:40:11.28,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,No, my disappointment...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.82,0:40:15.53,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...is in these men.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.83,0:40:17.83,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,For though I stand...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.08,0:40:20.16,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...among 10,000...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.50,0:40:21.96,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...I am alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.04,0:40:27.42,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,I long for a soul  who would stand by my side.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.67,0:40:28.84,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Who I could trust.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.89,0:40:37.18,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me, General Kashani.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.81,0:40:39.64,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you that man?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.52,0:40:44.77,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,You will taste your victory by the day's end.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.23,0:40:47.56,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,I will make certain of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.82,0:40:50.61,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope so.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.20,0:42:24.37,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Advance!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.50,0:42:35.05,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,NOW!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.74,0:43:01.03,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't lose sight of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.38,0:43:19.22,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,The Greeks are retreating.  He's got him right where he wants him.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.47,0:43:21.34,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Kashani is a fine tactician.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.97,0:43:24.64,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,I was speaking of Themistokles.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.48,0:43:35.52,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Rocks!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.69,0:43:40.20,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop, stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.45,0:43:41.74,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.45,0:43:44.16,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Brace yourselves!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.95,0:46:31.37,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.62,0:46:35.12,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,A man's responsibility  is to protect his family and his nation.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.37,0:46:38.33,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,- Who told you this?  - My father.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.77,0:47:44.77,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,You see how Themistokles  employs deception with such grace?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.28,0:47:48.19,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,- Why is it so much to ask for victory?  - How can I make amends?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.44,0:47:49.82,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Silence.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.24,0:47:55.62,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,You will carry a message for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.70,0:47:58.12,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Now they will fear us!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.37,0:48:02.00,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Now they will fear  the Greek men-at-arms! Hup!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.58,0:48:04.59,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,He's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.34,0:48:07.21,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Fear the Greek fighting man.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.46,0:48:08.59,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Fear his sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.84,0:48:10.17,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,His shield.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.63,0:48:13.22,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Fear his love for Mother Greece.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.47,0:48:14.97,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,But most of all...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.55,0:48:17.22,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...fear his freedom!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.27,0:48:25.19,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be angry with the boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.48,0:48:26.77,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,I took him under my command.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.02,0:48:30.03,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Anger is something I reserve  for my enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.29,0:48:39.87,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Themistokles.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.18,0:49:03.89,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Artemisia's ship is being anchored  in neutral waters.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.14,0:49:06.31,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,She'd like to meet with Themistokles.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.56,0:49:09.44,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,- How can you guarantee his safe return?  - Well, boy...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.69,0:49:11.61,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...the only honor for her now...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.86,0:49:15.24,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...will be when she watches  your crushed and broken fleet...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.49,0:49:17.41,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...sinking to the bottom of the Aegean...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.66,0:49:19.24,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...and is able to recognize you...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.49,0:49:22.58,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...nailed to the mast of your ship  with her sword...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.83,0:49:25.58,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...as you descend to a watery grave.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.96,0:49:33.47,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you just say that to begin with?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.91,0:50:03.41,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome to my humble barge.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.66,0:50:06.21,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,We are honored by your presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.67,0:50:10.92,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Your barge and you...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.63,0:50:13.26,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...are quite impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.05,0:50:19.89,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Kind words.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.51,0:50:24.73,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Now come, Themistokles.  We have much to discuss.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.44,0:50:29.10,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you believe the Greeks  are descended from the gods?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.36,0:50:30.94,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,I have heard some say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.19,0:50:34.48,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,And what of you?  ls there a god in your lineage?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.74,0:50:38.16,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,My men say so, and based on  the last two days' battle...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.66,0:50:41.91,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...I'd say there's a spark of the divine in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.12,0:50:45.70,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Now who's using kind words?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.59,0:50:54.17,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,My men also say that it was you...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.42,0:50:57.59,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...who slayed the good King Darius  at Marathon.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.84,0:51:00.26,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Many heroic deeds occurred on that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.51,0:51:02.22,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,But it was 10 years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.47,0:51:04.97,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...and the facts of battle  are often embellished.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.22,0:51:07.06,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,This deed, you would remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.39,0:51:11.52,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,I do what I must to defend Greece.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.77,0:51:14.32,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,And I do what I must to defeat her.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.44,0:51:20.45,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,For every one Greek killed,  you must kill a thousand Persians.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.45,0:51:24.12,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,For every ship I sink...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.08,0:51:26.87,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...you must sink a hundred.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.87,0:51:29.87,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,I can sustain losses for weeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.12,0:51:32.42,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Months, if need be.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.67,0:51:34.17,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,My numbers will defeat you...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.42,0:51:37.13,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...and I will take your precious boats  with my sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.38,0:51:38.97,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,I will take your Greek freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.68,0:51:42.51,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you asking me  to negotiate a surrender?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.76,0:51:43.80,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.81,0:51:47.77,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,I offer you a chance  to avoid such misery and join me.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.35,0:51:51.90,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm in need of a commander such as you.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.90,0:51:54.52,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at the defense you've mounted.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.57,0:51:58.03,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,A handful of triremes.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.86,0:52:01.35,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Leonidas with 300 Spartans.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.86,0:52:04.07,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,It's insulting, frankly...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.33,0:52:07.45,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...that the mightiest empire the world  has ever seen is met by this.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.62,0:52:11.79,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't blame you, Themistokles.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.62,0:52:15.38,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,You fought as if the blood  of Poseidon himself...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.63,0:52:17.75,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...was coursing through your veins.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.01,0:52:19.92,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I blame Greece.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.84,0:52:23.84,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,The squabbling bureaucrats  protecting their political hides...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.09,0:52:26.97,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...by sending you here to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.35,0:52:32.64,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,And yet you still fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.23,0:52:36.02,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,So there must be...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.69,0:52:38.98,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.32,0:52:44.32,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Family back home in Athens  that compels you...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.41,0:52:48.03,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...to battle with such passion?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.29,0:52:52.87,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Truth is, I've had no time for family.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.12,0:52:55.58,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,I have spent my entire adult life...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.83,0:52:57.63,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...with my one true love...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.59,0:53:00.17,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...the Greek fleet...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.92,0:53:02.76,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...and my one passion...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.01,0:53:04.89,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...readying it for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.06,0:53:10.56,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, that brings me pleasure...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.81,0:53:14.27,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...the thought of you pining away for me...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.19,0:53:17.77,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...forsaking family and love...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.02,0:53:21.19,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...for the promise of a deeper ecstasy.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.24,0:53:31.66,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,The ecstasy of steel and flesh...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.83,0:53:35.79,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...death and life...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.63,0:53:39.17,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...of rage...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.05,0:53:42.38,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...and sweat of muscle...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.51,0:53:45.43,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...of pure joy...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.43,0:53:48.60,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...and deepest sorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.85,0:53:53.68,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Die with me each night and be born again  with me each morning...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.35,0:53:58.23,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...as you plant your sword  into the hearts of our enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.98,0:54:03.65,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,You fight for freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.19,0:54:07.95,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,I offer freedom without  consequence or responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.20,0:54:12.66,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Join me...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.12,0:54:15.83,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...at my side.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.12,0:54:20.13,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Breathe each breath with me  as if it were your last.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.19,0:56:10.70,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Join me.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.74,0:56:17.95,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.09,0:56:32.34,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,You're no god. You're just a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.48,0:56:49.73,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Be quick with your sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.20,0:56:55.41,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll not have your death tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.95,0:56:57.12,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Guards!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.74,0:57:00.91,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Remove this filth from my ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.94,0:57:27.94,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.90,0:57:30.78,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,What have you learned?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.12,0:57:40.08,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Can Artemisia be beaten?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.79,0:57:44.08,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,The next time that we face her...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.33,0:57:46.96,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...she's going to bring all of hell with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.89,0:58:43.31,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold! Hold!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.86,0:58:56.95,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Send in my personal guard.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.85,0:59:24.85,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Pull back!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.10,0:59:26.18,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Retreat!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.43,0:59:27.56,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,- Retreat!  - Retreat!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.81,0:59:29.31,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,- Retreat!  - Retreat!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.02,0:59:31.73,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Themistokles!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.98,0:59:33.48,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,In the water!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.03,0:59:39.20,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Archers on deck now!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.45,0:59:41.11,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Archers on deck now! Quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:41.70,0:59:42.82,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Starboard side!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.08,0:59:44.24,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Fire at will!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.90,1:01:02.27,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Fight on, boy.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.45,1:01:03.49,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.74,1:01:05.20,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Fight on!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.01,1:01:26.72,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Aim for the men on top!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.97,1:01:28.18,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,UP there!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:38.71,1:02:41.55,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Abandon ship! Abandon ship!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.80,1:02:43.76,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Abandon ship!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:29.53,1:04:31.86,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,The dead have no guilt.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.41,1:04:34.62,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,No responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.83,1:04:37.99,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Themistokles watches the bodies  of his men...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.24,1:04:41.08,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...turn the Aegean red with blood.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:42.12,1:04:43.96,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Were they sacrificed for his ego?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:45.67,1:04:49.67,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Or to relieve the guilt of the long-ago  mistake at Marathon?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.68,1:04:54.38,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,How many men would have been saved...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.64,1:04:57.60,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...if Themistokles had killed that boy?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.35,1:05:03.10,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Not even his own soul can be sure.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.56,1:05:06.19,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,My friend.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.11,1:05:09.07,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,We faced the odds.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.40,1:05:11.99,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Together.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.99,1:05:14.99,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen to me...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.24,1:05:17.12,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...Themistokles.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.70,1:05:22.87,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,You will have to fight...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.12,1:05:25.92,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...with twice as much strength  in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.79,1:05:28.79,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,We will fight shoulder-to-shoulder.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.05,1:05:30.42,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,No, my son.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:31.88,1:05:34.63,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,You will carry on for both of us.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.94,1:06:35.36,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,What did he say?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.91,1:06:40.16,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,I will tell you in time, boy.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:42.41,1:06:43.74,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Quiet now.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:45.08,1:06:47.50,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,You go and be with your father's spirit.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.67,1:06:59.43,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,How many times do you think  we will repeat such a tragedy?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.97,1:07:02.14,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,As many times as we must.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:03.22,1:07:05.06,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,We are turning young men into memories.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.69,1:07:10.61,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think I enjoy this?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:12.15,1:07:14.15,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Witnessing my friend's final breath?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:18.07,1:07:20.41,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Every widow that is made by my decision...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:22.49,1:07:25.20,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...every child that will grow  without a father...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:27.00,1:07:28.75,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...they are my choices.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:29.75,1:07:33.38,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the burden of my command.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:57.28,1:07:58.90,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,How easy it is to silence...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.15,1:08:02.37,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...the strong and self-disciplined.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.62,1:08:05.79,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Let my army witness  the great warriors of Sparta.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:09.04,1:08:12.21,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,March them past these corpses.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.46,1:08:15.63,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Let them see the cost  of daring to challenge the god-king.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.38,1:08:20.93,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,King Leonidas...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.18,1:08:25.18,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...and his brave 300  were the finest Greece has to offer.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:25.47,1:08:26.72,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,There will be no saviors...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:26.97,1:08:29.39,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...to rise up and vanquish us.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.02,1:08:32.81,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing will stop the march of my empire.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:35.36,1:08:36.52,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Your Majesty.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.36,1:08:41.32,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,You, take this dead king's sword...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:41.57,1:08:42.86,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...to Athens.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.11,1:08:46.03,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Let them know  that I am coming next for them.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.20,1:08:48.79,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Let them know...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.04,1:08:50.54,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...Athens...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:51.25,1:08:54.13,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...their prize jewel of a city...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.92,1:08:57.34,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...will disappear from the histories.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:01.01,1:09:02.42,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Themistokles!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.51,1:09:06.51,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,I bring word...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.76,1:09:09.39,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...from Thermopylae.  Leonidas was betrayed by a hunchback.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:09.64,1:09:11.31,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,The Spartans have been slaughtered.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:11.56,1:09:12.77,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,The Hot Gates have fallen.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:15.77,1:09:17.81,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Such a sacrifice.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:21.94,1:09:24.11,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Now Greece has her martyrs.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:25.37,1:09:27.53,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Daxos, take that message...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:27.78,1:09:29.33,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...from the Hot Gates...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:29.58,1:09:31.91,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...to every city, every village.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.16,1:09:34.75,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Let every countryman hear your words.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:35.00,1:09:36.79,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,But they are dead. All of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:37.04,1:09:39.84,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Sparta's sacrifice will be what unites us.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.42,1:09:41.80,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Now go.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.05,1:09:43.63,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Hyah!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.84,1:09:46.59,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Move all of our ships and men back  to the safety of Salamis.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:46.84,1:09:48.22,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,And you?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:49.06,1:09:51.31,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,I will take Daxos' message to Athens.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:52.52,1:09:55.77,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,I was told a hunchback  was accountable for the fall of the Hot Gates.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:57.19,1:10:00.27,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,That he sold out his country...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.53,1:10:03.74,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...pulled the crimson from his back  and replaced it with Persian gold.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:06.49,1:10:08.28,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,What is your name, traitor?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:09.37,1:10:12.49,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Ephialtes of Trachis.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.42,1:10:28.43,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,I should wet this noble blade  with your blood.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:30.18,1:10:32.02,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,You would be right to do so.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.85,1:10:35.52,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,There is little beauty about me.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:35.77,1:10:39.77,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,There is little beauty in what I have done.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:44.61,1:10:46.28,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Say what you must.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:46.95,1:10:48.78,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,I beg of you...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:49.37,1:10:50.87,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...and all of Athens!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:51.12,1:10:54.66,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,The god-king will burn this city  to the ground!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:54.91,1:10:55.96,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,What does he mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:56.50,1:10:58.17,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Quiet yourselves!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:59.13,1:11:03.13,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Leonidas' and Sparta's great sacrifice  was no defeat.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:06.26,1:11:08.34,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a beautiful victory.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:11.64,1:11:14.10,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,This simple act of valor...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:14.39,1:11:16.85,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...will allow us to rally each  of our city-states...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:17.10,1:11:19.10,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...and unite Greece...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.98,1:11:21.98,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...for one purpose...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.31,1:11:23.48,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...against one enemy!
Dialogue: 0,1:11:24.90,1:11:25.94,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,And you.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:26.19,1:11:29.45,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,You take this message to your god-king.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:29.70,1:11:32.24,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,That we will take whatever ships  we have left...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:32.78,1:11:35.24,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...and finish this in the Bay of Salamis.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.12,1:11:38.71,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,But there will be death and destruction.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:38.96,1:11:42.75,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, there will be.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:49.51,1:11:50.93,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Themistokles.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:53.26,1:11:55.43,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm here to speak to your queen.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:56.18,1:11:57.68,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,A warning, Athenian.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:57.93,1:12:00.69,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,You may not receive a warm welcome.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:27.46,1:12:30.05,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,May I offer my deepest sympathies.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:31.68,1:12:34.51,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,I cannot change what has happened  to Leonidas...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:34.76,1:12:37.60,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...but his sacrifice will not be forgotten.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:38.56,1:12:42.02,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Do not lecture me on sacrifice,  and be quick with your words, Athenian.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:44.90,1:12:48.15,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,I request of you the entire Spartan navy.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:48.90,1:12:50.49,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Every man, every ship...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:50.74,1:12:53.07,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,-...that you can spare.  - Have I not given enough...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:53.32,1:12:55.11,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...for your dream of a united Greece?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:55.37,1:12:58.74,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Shall I put swords in the hands  of my son? Our children?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:58.99,1:13:00.20,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Would that please you?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:01.66,1:13:05.17,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Have I not given enough  for your ambitions, Themistokles?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:05.42,1:13:06.96,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,A king.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:07.67,1:13:10.05,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Husbands, fathers, brothers.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:10.30,1:13:12.76,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Sparta will give no more.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:28.44,1:13:30.31,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,This belongs with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.24,1:13:41.70,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Avenge him.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:59.68,1:14:02.43,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,The Oracle's words stood as a warning.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:03.18,1:14:05.35,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,All of Greece will fall...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:05.73,1:14:09.27,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...as Persian fire reduces Athens to cinder.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:10.48,1:14:12.82,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,For Athens is a pile of stone and wood...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:13.07,1:14:15.66,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...and cloth and dust...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:16.57,1:14:19.37,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...and, as dust, will vanish into the wind.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:21.03,1:14:23.83,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Only the Athenians themselves exist.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:25.04,1:14:28.62,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,And the fate of the world  hangs on their every syllable.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.50,1:14:31.88,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Only the Athenians exist.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:32.25,1:14:35.22,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,And only stout wooden ships can save them.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:35.88,1:14:37.47,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Wooden ships...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:38.26,1:14:41.10,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...and a tidal wave of heroes' blood.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:48.19,1:14:51.27,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,The Greeks were fools to stand against us.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:51.52,1:14:53.15,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Leonidas and his pride...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:53.40,1:14:55.99,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...were no match for the will of a god.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:58.28,1:15:02.20,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Themistokles was a worthless coward.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:02.45,1:15:03.95,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,And now...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:04.50,1:15:08.21,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...this pathetic navy  is barely worth our attention.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:08.46,1:15:10.75,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,If that worthless coward  had stood at my side...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:11.00,1:15:12.59,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...we would have laid the world...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:12.84,1:15:14.33,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...at your feet.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:14.84,1:15:15.96,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,My king.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:17.17,1:15:20.68,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Your humble servant brings you news.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:22.01,1:15:24.39,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,The Greek fleet are defenseless...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:24.64,1:15:27.22,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...within the Bay of Salamis.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.48,1:15:29.94,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,You need only finish them.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:30.86,1:15:32.52,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Who commands their forces?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:36.03,1:15:38.53,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Themistokles of Athens.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:38.78,1:15:40.61,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Themistokles is dead.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:40.86,1:15:44.33,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,He is alive. I have seen him myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:58.63,1:16:00.43,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Ready my troops and armor.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:00.68,1:16:01.97,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,We will attack at once.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:02.22,1:16:03.22,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Wisdom...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:04.68,1:16:05.68,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...would have us...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:05.93,1:16:08.60,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...send a probing force to confirm  it is not a trap.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:09.77,1:16:12.02,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,You would dare to advise me  in matters of war?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:13.65,1:16:15.57,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,I am the god-king.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:15.82,1:16:18.53,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,I am the one who triumphed over Leonidas.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:18.78,1:16:20.82,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,I am the one who laid waste...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:21.07,1:16:22.87,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...to this showpiece of Athens.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:23.12,1:16:26.29,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,- I am your king.  - Killing Leonidas and his men...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:26.54,1:16:28.71,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...only made them martyrs.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:29.58,1:16:31.58,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,And when you razed Athens...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:32.21,1:16:33.87,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...you set fire to the only thing...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:34.13,1:16:36.12,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...of value in this country.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:48.06,1:16:50.48,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,I will attack the Greeks...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:51.64,1:16:54.23,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...with my entire navy.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:55.44,1:16:56.57,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Artemisia.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:56.82,1:16:58.15,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Enough!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:59.65,1:17:03.03,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Do not forget who put the crown  on your childish head.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:03.61,1:17:05.24,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,My king.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:06.33,1:17:07.83,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Now sit on your golden throne...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:08.08,1:17:10.75,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...and watch this battle  from the safety I provide you.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:17.04,1:17:18.71,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,There in the distance...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:19.92,1:17:22.67,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...we witness the destruction of Athens.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:26.22,1:17:30.22,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Alone, we will face the monster  that cast a shadow across our land.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:33.31,1:17:36.94,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,I had prayed that the Spartans  would come to lend a hand this morning.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:39.98,1:17:41.90,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps they feel they have given enough.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:42.15,1:17:43.57,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,You failed us all.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:43.82,1:17:45.20,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,This is your fault, Themistokles.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:45.45,1:17:47.03,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Without Spartans, we're farmhands.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:47.28,1:17:49.33,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,We should've negotiated  with the Persians when we had the chance.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:54.25,1:17:55.96,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,You are all right.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:57.79,1:18:01.55,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, we are down to a handful of boats.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:02.63,1:18:06.09,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,And, yes, we are just farmhands.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:06.80,1:18:08.55,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,We are tradesmen.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:09.68,1:18:10.76,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,We are boys...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:11.43,1:18:15.14,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...turned to men through the sacrifice  and forge of combat.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:17.61,1:18:19.94,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,I played a dangerous game...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:20.19,1:18:21.78,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...and I lost!
Dialogue: 0,1:18:26.66,1:18:29.99,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,If you choose to turn your back on me...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:30.45,1:18:31.83,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...on your country...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:35.12,1:18:37.04,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...I will not judge you.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:38.71,1:18:40.75,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,You are free to leave.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:41.84,1:18:43.92,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,You are still free men.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:07.07,1:19:08.24,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:10.16,1:19:11.16,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Then let us...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:11.41,1:19:15.37,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...put our shoulders to work  and free those ships from the bosom of Greece.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:17.71,1:19:20.38,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Today is a privilege to call our own.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:21.71,1:19:25.30,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,A story that will be told  for a thousand years.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:26.47,1:19:28.47,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Let our final stand...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:28.72,1:19:30.76,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...be recorded to the histories.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:31.22,1:19:33.01,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,And let it be shown...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:33.60,1:19:36.18,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...that we chose to die on our feet...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:36.43,1:19:38.77,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...rather than live on our knees!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:26.90,1:20:29.28,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,There is only one thing  you need to know today.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:29.53,1:20:31.03,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Not to get killed.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:31.28,1:20:35.28,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,No. Your father's last words.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:39.37,1:20:42.42,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,He told me that you had earned  the right to sit at the table.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:59.68,1:21:03.69,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, my brother,  I have no more tactics or tricks.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:05.48,1:21:07.86,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,This will be the last battle that we share.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:08.11,1:21:11.74,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,We have fought next to one other  for as long as I can remember.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:12.57,1:21:15.95,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing would please me more  than to rest this sword.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:17.12,1:21:20.70,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,- The preparations that are required?  - Below deck.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:21.79,1:21:23.71,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,- Good.  - Are you sure...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:23.96,1:21:25.75,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...that you want to commit everything?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:26.46,1:21:27.54,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:29.38,1:21:32.26,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Without Artemisia's command,  the Persian navy is nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:34.01,1:21:36.14,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,We will never be able to reach her.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:36.39,1:21:37.93,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,I will reach her...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:38.72,1:21:40.64,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...and put an end to this.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:41.56,1:21:44.30,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,There will be no room for a retreat.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:45.40,1:21:46.81,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:49.19,1:21:52.61,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Today the last Greek ships will be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:52.86,1:21:54.95,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Show them no mercy.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:55.20,1:21:57.70,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Give them no quarter.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:57.95,1:22:01.16,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Today we will dance across the backs  of dead Greeks.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:01.87,1:22:04.62,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Today we deliver submission.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:05.50,1:22:07.54,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Today I want to feel Themistokles' throat...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:07.83,1:22:09.79,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...beneath my boots.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:40.62,1:22:43.08,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Men, brace yourselves!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:37.22,1:23:38.80,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Prepare for close quarters.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:39.05,1:23:40.55,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Attack!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:46.68,1:23:47.81,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Your father watches you!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:49.19,1:23:51.36,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold nothing back!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:51.60,1:23:52.94,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Seize your glory!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:21.30,1:24:23.85,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not here as a witness.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:25.62,1:25:26.62,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,NOW!
Dialogue: 0,1:25:27.41,1:25:30.65,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,And let them send our souls straight to hell!
Dialogue: 0,1:26:07.62,1:26:10.16,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Hyah! Come on!
Dialogue: 0,1:27:16.89,1:27:18.44,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,You offered freedom without...
Dialogue: 0,1:27:18.69,1:27:21.65,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,-...consequence or responsibility.  - Are you accepting my offer?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:21.90,1:27:23.36,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,My answer is still no.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:51.97,1:27:54.35,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,You fight much harder than you fuck.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:37.89,1:28:40.56,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Surrender to me or meet your death.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:40.81,1:28:41.94,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Who would you fight...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:42.19,1:28:43.44,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...if not for me?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:44.06,1:28:46.28,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,No one could challenge your skill.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:46.52,1:28:49.48,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,I would rather die a free man than as a slave.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:50.61,1:28:53.07,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if the chain was attached to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:02.21,1:29:04.67,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,It begins as a whisper.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:05.46,1:29:07.09,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,A promise.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:08.13,1:29:09.46,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,The lightest of breezes...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:09.71,1:29:11.20,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...dances through the rigging...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:11.22,1:29:14.30,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...as it creaks above the death cries  of 10,000 men.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:15.68,1:29:19.27,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,It moves through her hair  as gently as a lover's hand.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:19.64,1:29:20.64,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,That breeze...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:21.94,1:29:25.77,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...that promise, became a wind,  a wind that is blown across Greece...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:26.02,1:29:28.48,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...carrying a message told again and again...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:28.73,1:29:31.69,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...of our Lady Freedom  and how wise she was...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:31.95,1:29:35.70,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...to charge Leonidas to lay all at her feet.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:37.37,1:29:40.24,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,A wind, my brothers, of sacrifice.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:42.12,1:29:44.04,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,A wind of freedom.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:46.25,1:29:48.42,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,A wind of justice.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:56.09,1:29:58.14,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,A wind of vengeance.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:21.04,1:30:22.79,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah-ooh! Ah-ooh! Ah-ooh!
Dialogue: 0,1:30:42.60,1:30:43.85,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,You are being surrounded.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:44.35,1:30:47.27,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,All of Greece has united against you.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:47.90,1:30:50.82,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Delphi, Thebes, Olympia...
Dialogue: 0,1:30:51.07,1:30:53.86,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,...Arcadia and Sparta.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:08.21,1:31:10.75,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,If death comes for me today, I'm ready.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:12.04,1:31:14.05,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,I could lower my sword.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:14.30,1:31:16.97,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,There's still time for you  to ready a launch and escape.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:21.26,1:31:24.85,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,It would be a poor choice  to force my hand into action.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:25.48,1:31:29.19,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Now order your ships to disengage  and surrender to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:31.61,1:31:33.27,Default_英文,,0000,0000,0000,,Surrender?

